cene 15 if you have not refused too many interactions.\"}]]}]\n7:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"font-[Epilogue] text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4\",\"children\":\"Lore Meaning\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-on-surface-variant text-sm\",\"children\":\"The Grand Finale represents the circus as a functioning performance — Harlequin completes her act, the audience applauds, and the curtain falls. It is the only ending that presents the circus as a normal entertainment venue, without the meta-narrative elements that appear in secret endings. Some community members interpret this as the \\\"intended\\\" ending before the player discovers the darker layers.\"}]]}]\n8:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"font-[Epilogue] text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4\",\"children\":\"Community Theory\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-on-surface-variant text-sm\",\"children\":\"The community theory suggests that The Grand Finale is a \\\"surface level\\\" ending — what the circus wants the player to see. Secret endings reveal that this performance is a loop, and that Harlequin has given this same performance countless times. The standard ending's simplicity makes it suspicious in retrospect.\"}]]}]\n9:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"font-[Epilogue] text-2xl font-bold text-foreground mb-4\",\"children\":\"FAQ\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"bg-surface-container border border-outline/20 p-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h3\",null,{\"className\":\"font-bold text-foreground mb-2\",\"children\":\"Can you get this ending on the first playthrough?\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-on-surface-variant text-sm\",\"children\":\"Yes. The Grand Finale is designed as the standard ending for Harlequin's route and requires no special conditions.\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null